# Create Config

When adding or reading configuration in `masterfabric_backend`:

- All config via environment variables (no hardcoded values).
- `internal/shared/config/config.go` is the single loader; add new fields there.
- Use `getEnv(key, fallback)` for strings, `getEnvInt` for ints, `envOrDefaultInt32` for int32 (gosec G115).
- DSN is parsed via `net/url` (passwords with `@:/?#%` are safe).
- Sensible defaults for development; `.env.example` maintained with all required vars.
- Secrets (`JWT_SECRET`, `DATABASE_DSN`, `REDIS_URL`) never logged or exposed in error responses.
- Startup warns when `JWT_SECRET == "change-me-in-production"`.

## Checklist
- [ ] All config via env vars
- [ ] Sensible defaults for development
- [ ] Connection pooling configured (`DB_MAX_CONNS`, `DB_MIN_CONNS`)
- [ ] `.env.example` maintained
- [ ] Secrets never logged or exposed in errors
